Number in Records: Number to the left of the name. Order of person in the records.
Last Name: Last name listed in records under "Name"
First Name: First name listed in records under "Name"
Unabvreviated First Name: This feild corresponds to the unabbrevated version of the listed first name (if there is an abbreviation)
Assumed Gender: This field corresponds to the gender of the person that the data collectors assumed when completing the Blockley Census
Age: Age at the time of this census
Social State: This feild corresponds to the persons relationship status (for adults) or lists if they are a child
Habits: How often the person consumes alcohol or other substances
Literacy (Read or Write): This feild corresponds to whether or not the person could read or write
# of times: This feild corresponds to the number of times a person has been in Blockley
Disease: Any report diseases a person has
Time in Alms House: This feild corresponds to the amount of time the person has spent in the Alms House during their current stay (if they have been in Blockley multiple times)
